    Class Description
    SupportUtils
    The SupportUtils class is containing various methods to check if the device supports NFC authentication.
    Utils
    The Utils class is containing various methods to make often-needed tasks as HTTP requests.
    VolleyResponse
    The class VolleyResponse represents the string after Volley finishes The class includes 1 field corresponding to the response of the Volley HTTP request, the getter: VolleyResponse.getResponse(), setter: VolleyResponse.setResponse(JSONObject), for this field and 3 constructors: {VolleyResponse.VolleyResponse(), VolleyResponse.VolleyResponse(String), VolleyResponse.VolleyResponse(JSONObject)} to initialize value to the field VolleyResponse.response and some other procedures: {VolleyResponse.onSuccess(String), VolleyResponse.toString(), VolleyResponse.hashCode(), VolleyResponse.equals(Object)}.
